    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You form a 30-foot cone by using chakra to generate molecule sized particles. Anyone in the cone will begin to be deconstructed on a molecular level. Creatures in its path must succeed a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure a creature takes 12d6 force damage. If a creature is reduced to less than ½ of their hit points. The user decides on which appendage the target creature lost. (Arm or Leg). If a creature is reduced to 0 hit points, they are turned to dust and are immediately killed.</p>",
